column2: "He picked up the knife and stabbed me."
column3: "I tripped and fell, and the knife on the floor stabbed me."
column4: "There was an arrow wedged in the floor, and I got stabbed when I fell into it."
column5: "The knife fell off the counter, and stabbed my foot."
column6: "I got stabbed by a knife that was lying on the floor."
column7: "I was stabbed by a falling arrow."
column8: "He threw the knife, which spun across the room and stabbed me."
column9: "He picked up an arrow from the ground, and stabbed me with it."
column10: "The archers in the treetops stabbed me with arrows from their bows."
column11: "He stabbed me by throwing the knife at me."
column12: "I was inadvertently stabbed as we tussled."
column13: "The soldiers hurled their spears at me, stabbing me several times."
